# Token Efficiency Rules

## Reading code

- Use `Grep` for finding symbols — never `Read` a whole file to find one function
- Use `Read` with `offset` + `limit` to read only the needed lines
- Use `Glob` to find files by pattern before reading
- Use `gitnexus query/context` first — often replaces reading 3–5 files

## Editing code

- `StrReplace` for targeted edits — never rewrite an entire file unless <80 lines
- One `StrReplace` call per logical change
- Batch independent tool calls in a single message

## Shell

- Combine commands with `&&` in one Shell call instead of sequential calls
- Use `head -n 20` or `grep` to inspect large outputs instead of reading everything

## Analysis

- Run Python analysis inline in Shell — do NOT create temporary `.py` files
- Reuse computed data within a single shell call rather than chaining multiple calls

## Subagent delegation

- Delegate CSV analysis to `p300-analyst` agent (saves repeating the algorithm)
- Delegate code review to `eeg-reviewer` agent (saves repeating impact rules)
- Delegate logging to `session-logger` agent after each task

## Context hygiene

- Never repeat information already established in the conversation
- Reference `docs/AI_LOG.md` for project history instead of re-explaining
